================================================================================

The Dataarm desktop application is distributed as a native Tauri bundle that
includes:

  - compiled Rust crates from crates.io and pinned upstream git dependencies
  - bundled frontend assets built from npm packages

The authoritative dependency inventories for a given release are recorded in:

  - src-tauri/Cargo.lock
  - package-lock.json

The shipped macOS application bundle also carries these maintained legal files
under Contents/SharedSupport/Legal:

  - LICENSE
  - NOTICE
  - PATENTS.md
  - Cargo.lock
  - package-lock.json

This NOTICE summarizes the maintained license posture for public distribution.
It intentionally points to the lockfiles and package metadata as the source of
truth rather than trying to freeze every package name in prose.

For executable-form distribution, the corresponding Dataarm source form and the
maintained legal files are published from the same repository and release flow
that produces the public DMG.

For a fuller Rust license report, run:
  cargo install cargo-about
  cargo about generate about.hbs --manifest-path src-tauri/Cargo.toml

For npm package metadata, inspect:
  node_modules/*/package.json
  package-lock.json

================================================================================
Rust dependency license policy
================================================================================

The Rust dependency policy enforced by deny.toml currently allows these SPDX
license families:

  Apache-2.0
  BSD-3-Clause
  CDLA-Permissive-2.0
  ISC
  MIT
  Unicode-3.0
  Zlib

It also carries scoped MPL-2.0 exceptions for CSS selector and parser crates:

  cssparser
  cssparser-macros
  dtoa-short
  htmlcut-selectors
  option-ext
  selectors

The embedded runtime surface includes pinned upstream git dependencies from:

  https://github.com/resoltico/ffhn.git
  https://github.com/resoltico/HTMLCut.git

Those sources are allowed explicitly in deny.toml and are version-locked in
src-tauri/Cargo.lock.

================================================================================
Frontend package metadata
================================================================================

Installed npm package metadata in the maintained Dataarm toolchain currently
reports the following license families:

  Apache-2.0
  Apache-2.0 OR MIT
  BlueOak-1.0.0
  BSD-2-Clause
  BSD-3-Clause
  CC-BY-4.0
  CC0-1.0
  ISC
  MIT
  MIT-0
  MPL-2.0

Representative packages from the maintained surface include:

  react, react-dom, vite, vitest, eslint       - MIT
  @tauri-apps/api, @tauri-apps/cli             - Apache-2.0 OR MIT
  typescript                                   - Apache-2.0
  lightningcss                                 - MPL-2.0
  caniuse-lite                                 - CC-BY-4.0
  mdn-data                                     - CC0-1.0

The exact package-by-package obligations for any release are controlled by the
license texts shipped by those packages and the inventories recorded in
package-lock.json and src-tauri/Cargo.lock.

